# Homework (Individual) 
- Part I
    - I want a plot that shows me, for each ward, the fraction of the precincts where the winner of the ward beat the runner up in the ward.
    - The plot should show all wards, be properly labeled, easy to read, etc.
    - The doc should use the template, and write it up like it is going to your (potential) boss
    - Grading on this homework will be according to the rubric in the course outline...and will be tougher than the first one!
- Part II
    - I tossed a coin and got these results:
        x <- c("t", "t", "h", "t", "h", "h", "t", "t", "t", "t", "t", "t", "h", "h", "t", "h", "t", "t", "t", "t", "t", "h", "t", "t", "h", "t")
    - Do a **different** hypothesis test to see if the coin is fair
        - note just calculating by hand what one of the built in functions does is **not** different
    - Please be painfully explicit about what you are assuming
- due Oct 1, 23:59


